Validation
===============================================================================

1. Overview
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Validation uses invariants to check program integrity at runtime and during `mech test`.

```mech:disabled
foo! := EXPRESSION
```

An invariant name ends with `!`, and its expression must evaluate to `<bool>`.

2. Full file example
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

```mech:disabled
+> math/sqrt

x := 9
root := sqrt(x)

root-is-positive! := root >= 0
round-trip! := root * root == x
```

3. Running tests
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

`mech test` runs the supplied files and reports invariant results.

```sh
mech test program.mec
mech test tests/program.mec --verbose
```

When the argument is a directory, `mech test` discovers Mech files under that directory and evaluates their invariants as one test run.

```sh
mech test .
mech test tests
```

4. CI example
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

```sh
mech test . --verbose -o report.json
```

Use a non-zero exit status from `mech test` to fail CI when an invariant fails or a file cannot be loaded.

5. Related documentation
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

See `docs/getting-started/build-and-run.mec` for CLI usage and `docs/reference/modules.mec` for importing shared test helpers.
